# Cursor Rules for Baccarat Assistant

## CSS and Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- @apply directive is valid and should not be flagged as an error
- @tailwind, @layer, @screen, @variants, @responsive are all valid Tailwind directives
- Prefer utility classes over custom CSS when possible
- Use @apply sparingly, only for component-level abstractions

## Vue 3 + TypeScript
- Use Composition API with <script setup>
- Prefer TypeScript interfaces over types
- Use Pinia for state management
- Follow Vue 3 best practices

## Code Quality
- ESLint and Prettier are configured
- Follow conventional commit messages
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions

## Tailwind CSS Configuration
- Project uses Tailwind CSS v3.4.17
- PostCSS is configured with tailwindcss and autoprefixer
- Custom CSS should use @layer directive when needed
- Unknown at-rules should be ignored in CSS validation 